participating-org.narrative:
VIFEP is a public research organization, belonging to the Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development (MARD), having the functions of capture fisheries, aquaculture, processing and seafood trading policy analysis and institutional arrangements;  researching on seafood sectoral economic and social issues, fisheries and aquaculture development planning, baseline surveys; international cooperation and  training; technology transfer and other consultation services.

Research functions and capacity
As a leading research institution in the field of fisheries  economics and planning, VIFEP has been carrying out various research mandates and activities related to sustainable fisheries development in Vietnam:
(1) Research and develop long-term, five-years and annual strategies, planning and programs, projects on fisheries economic and development planning within the Institute#s missions;
(2) Research and develop national standards and technical regulations; economic and technical procedures, regulations and guidelines under the Institute#s duties;
(3) Assess the effectiveness of policies, planning, programs and projects in the fields of fisheries; and evaluate the impacts of climate change, economic, social, cultural and environmental aspects related to fisheries development;
(4) Conduct surveys and studies on the socio-economic assessments and environment issues related to fisheries development, baseline study, cost <(>&<)> benefit analysis, resource economics, market economics, regional and local economics, environmental economics as well as social, cultural andenvironment issues and climate change related to fisheries resource management;
(5) Studies on seafood markets and seafood value chain analysis as well as fisheries management and organization models;
(6) Research and develop databases for markets, trade promotion, international economic integration; economic, cultural and social issues related to fisheries development; market forecasting forsupply and demand, and related issues for fisheries development.
(7) Research to apply GIS, remote sensing and other technologies to develop databases, mapping for planning projects and assist the decision making process in fisheries development.
